summary: An ordinance accepting a deed of conveyance from the Seattle Electric Company to the City of Seattle dated the 10th day of August, 1909, a strip of land lying and being in King County, State of Washington, more particularly described as follows to-wit: that portion of block 7, Craven's Division of Green Lake Addition to the City of Seattle, described as follows, to-wit: beginning at a point on the north line of said block, said point being distant one hundred sixteen and nine one-hundredths (116.09) feet west from the Northeast corner of said block; thence west along the north line thereof a distance of thirty and forty one-hundredths (30.40) feet; thence south 8 degrees, 59 minutes, 38 seconds east, a distance of 154.76 feet to a point on the southeasterly line of said block; thence northeasterly along said southeasterly line a distance of 40.48 feet; thence north 8 degrees, 59 minutes and 38 seconds west, a distance of 122.64 feet to the point of beginning.
